emails.subject: Student Life Blog: K9s at the Ville
emails.body:
Discover one of Cedarville's student ministries!

      Discover one of Cedarville's student ministries!    
                        ‚Ää                      
NEW STUDENT LIFE BLOG POSTS


                        ‚Ää                      


READ NOW <https://blogs.cedarville.edu/studentlife/2025/11/13/k9s-at-the-ville-service-dogs-cedarville-university/>

                        ‚Ää                      


How Students Are Changing Lives Four Paws at a Time


                                You might already be thinking about the many ministry opportunities you can get involved in at Cedarville. Today's blog post will give you an inside look at K9s at the Ville, an on-campus organization that trains service dogs to help children and veterans with disabilities. If you love pups and want to make a difference for those in need, K9s at the Ville might be just the right ministry for you!                              





                        ‚Ää                      


Hear From Our Junior: Eva


                                  Today's blog post from Eva shares stories of hope from K9s at the Ville trainers. You'll see Cedarville students' hearts for ministry ‚Äî and some really cute dogs too! üê∂

emails.subject: Wildcat Summer Academy: Save the Date - June 21-26, 2026!
emails.body:
Wildcat Summer Academic Camps Are Back!





WSA offers a unique, immersive experience on IWU's Marion campus, providing a taste of college life and learning. 

                                Designed for high school students entering ninth grade through graduating seniors, WSA blends hands-on learning with enriching social activates in a welcoming and supportive environment. Participants build valuable skills, engage with faculty, and explore their interests with peers from across the country.

                                The all-inclusive camps begin at $500 <https://www.indwes.edu/admissions/academic-youth-programs/summer-academy/#camps> and include room, food, and the campus experience.                               

Register fast, because spots fill quickly!





Explore Camps <https://www.indwes.edu/admissions/academic-youth-programs/summer-academy/#camps>

¬†

Beyond academics, Capital University is part of the charming community
of Bexley. Here, tree-lined Main Street is home to award-winning pizza
parlors, renowned ice cream shops, diverse restaurants, and cozy
coffee houses. With grocery stores, banks, salons, and a pharmacy
within walking distance, you'll feel right at home.

¬†

Whichever application you choose, you won't have to pay an application
fee and submitting your ACT/SAT scores is totally optional! We'll also
automatically consider you for scholarships.

¬†

All full-time, incoming undergraduate students receive the Main Street
Scholarship, an award starting at $80,000, applied over four years.
But the Main Street Scholarship is just the beginning! This
scholarship is "stackable," meaning that it can be combined with other
awards and aid, including:

* The Capital Merit Scholarship: Given for academic accomplishments
and based on GPA.

* The Comet Community Award: A $5,000 award for residential students
that is applied to housing.

* The Capital Gateway Scholarship: Full tuition and fees are awarded
to students who meet additional GPA, residency, and incoming
requirements.

Kieran, my team is looking forward to getting to
know you better as you navigate the enrollment process at Capital
University. Get started with the Capital Application [
https://my.gocapitalu.org/f/r/c5198d4ad32d1a61853c195cc?%3D&
] or the Common App [
https://my.gocapitalu.org/f/r/c5198d4ad32d1a61853c195cc?%3D&
] today!

¬†

Sincerely,

Derek Faasse

Capital University‚îÇ1 College and Main‚îÇColumbus, OH 43209

emails.subject: Academics boosted by real-world learning
emails.body:
It's a combo that makes UofL stand apart.

Bold thinking and real impact start here.


Apply Now <http://louisville.edu/admissions/apply?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics>
                                      Kieran, you know that lectures and textbooks alone won't prepare you for your dream career. To change the world, you need real-life opportunities to explore, experiment and succeed. That's why UofL's Center for Engaged Learning <https://student.louisville.edu/engaged-learning?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> empowers you to complete internships, research, co-ops and more. 

Check out this video <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=exBKNbL5kXw&utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> for a preview of how we encourage students to gain confidence and create lasting change: 
                                                                           

                                                                                                               At UofL, your education comes to life through:                                    

	 200+ academic programs <https://louisville.edu/academics?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> filled with hands-on experiences.                                      
	                                         Groundbreaking research opportunities <https://student.louisville.edu/engaged-learning/undergraduate-research?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics>.                                      
	 Three career centers <https://louisville.edu/career/?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> serving undergraduate students that prepare you for and connect you to internships and co-ops.                                      
	                                         A global education through our robust study abroad programs <https://louisville.edu/international/education-abroad?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics>.                                      

                                      And our school isn't just keeping up -- we're leading the field.                                    

	                                         We've been ranked in the Top 100 Public Schools <https://news.louisville.edu/news/uofl-earns-highest-ever-us-news-world-report-ranking?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> (again) by U.S. News & World Report.                                       
	                                         We've started a new Bachelor's in Communication Sciences and Disorders <https://catalog.louisville.edu/undergraduate/majors/communication-sciences-and-disorders-bs/?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> program that explores how we speak, hear and connect -- real preparation for careers in speech-language pathology or audiology.                                       
	                                         This September, we opened the state-of-the-art J.B. Speed School of Engineering's Student Success & Research Building <https://news.louisville.edu/news/uofl-speed-school-opens-90m-student-success-research-building-0?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics>. It features a makerspace that is open to students of all majors.                                       
	                                         Our University Honors Program <https://student.louisville.edu/honors?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> provides an elevated academic experience that's both rigorous and supportive. It combines small, discussion-based classes with big research opportunities, global travel experiences and hands-on impact. You'll have a built-in community from day one in our dedicated Honors residence hall.                                      

                                      UofL prepares you to enter the world as a confident leader who is connected to a community that always has your back. With our Border Benefit Award <https://louisville.edu/admissions/cost-aid/scholarships/uofl-regional-awards/border-benefit?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> lowering tuition to the in-state rate for qualifying students like you, there's even more reason to choose the University of Louisville.

Apply today <http://louisville.edu/admissions/apply?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics> to become a Cardinal!                                    




Apply to UofL <http://louisville.edu/admissions/apply?utm_campaign=border-benefit&utm_content=border-benefit-09&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=academics>



                                      Louisville, KY 40208
502-852-6531

emails.subject: So Many Majors. One Supportive Community
emails.body: With more than 70 areas of study, there‚Äôs a path for you. Kieran: College is the place to ask questions, explore your interests, and discover what drives you. Whether you know exactly what you want to do or need some help along the way, we've got you covered! At Manchester, we have more than 70 academic programs (https://emp.eduyield.com/el?aid=ec012a28-d16f-11f0-907b-02a21d2bf809&rid=137971704&pid=949200&cid=1011&dest=https%3A%2F%2Fapplyto.manchester.edu%2Fportal%2Flanding) covering exciting career areas like: Pre-Health Professions Business and Management Human Services/Social Work Nursing Education Psychology Human Performance Our many pre-professional tracks (like pre-law, pre-med and pre-vet) provide step-by-step guidance toward your goals. Or unleash your creativity and create an individualized major that brings together several areas that excite you. From career planning, research, and internships to campus jobs and study abroad, Manchester makes your personal growth a priority. (And with scholarships for every student, you‚Äôll find Manchester surprisingly affordable.) emails.subject: As You Reflect on 2025‚Ä¶ Picture Your 2026 at PBA
emails.body:
Dear Kieran,

Our 2025 highlights are in!

As you look back on the moments that shaped your year, from favorite memories to meaningful accomplishments, we invite you to look ahead to 2026 and imagine what new experiences could be this coming August.

If you are hoping in 2026 for academic growth, the opportunity to discover your God-given calling and be supported as you pursue it, new friendships and fun memories in a Christian community, life in a tropical downtown location one mile from the beach, and growth in your walk with Christ, then we know the perfect place for you: Palm Beach Atlantic University.

Take your first step toward making your dream college experience a reality! We invite you to complete your application <http://apply.pba.edu/apply> to PBA. Our application is free, test-optional, and requires no essay. Once you submit your application, simply send us your transcript(s), and you can expect an admissions decision within approximately 72 hours. 

                              Complete Your Application <https://apply.pba.edu/apply>



If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us by emailing admit@pba.edu or calling 561-803-2100. We'd be happy to help!

emails.subject: The secret to getting into the college of your dreams is‚Ä¶
emails.from: University of Pennsylvania Office of Admissions <info_at_admissions.upenn.edu_jkgwnjk4@duck.com>
emails.body:
Yes, we're really going to tell you!

Visit <https://admissions.upenn.edu/visit-connect/visit-penn?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>
My Profile <https://key.admissions.upenn.edu/register/inquiry?pid=hreii-DRHrmrThd-IVN-qrr8PEXoui8wzcKiwhBveE3eU10D3_0aOvjLqHFx3RR2HcDBUSISC1s&utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>
Ask <https://ask.admissions.upenn.edu/?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>
                      As you're researching and applying to colleges, you might be wondering‚Äîwhat's the secret formula to getting into the university of my dreams? Well, here at Penn, we believe in full transparency so we're here to give you all the tea to help you prepare your strongest application.                    

                      During the application review process, admissions officers (also referred to as AOs) are looking to see all of the qualities that make you uniquely you. So, before you press submit, ask yourself:                    


"In my application, have I made clear..."

...why I want to attend the school I'm applying to?

                      AOs want you to hear all about what subjects, programs, and activities on campus are especially exciting to you.
Learn more > <https://admissions.upenn.edu/how-to-apply/preparing-your-application/writing?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>


...how I've spent my time the last four years and why?

                      AOs want you to paint a full picture of who you are‚Äîincluding outside the classroom‚Äîthrough your extracurriculars, responsibilities at home, and your service to your community.
Learn more > <https://admissions.upenn.edu/how-to-apply/preparing-your-application/activities?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>


...what's important to me, what interests me, and what I plan for my future?

                      AOs want to get insight into how the school you're applying to and their community fit into your present and how your time there will shape your future.
Learn more > <https://admissions.upenn.edu/student-life/exploring-community?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>


...how I engage with the communities I'm a part of?

                      When you join a school, you won't just be an island on your own‚Äîyou'll become part of a community. How have you contributed to communities you've been a part of? How might you influence your new school, and let your new surroundings influence you?
Learn more > <https://youtu.be/O5knZ0GNVGg?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>


Tips From Penn Admissions

                      As you prepare your application, make sure you review all of the elements of the comprehensive process at the colleges you're applying to. And it doesn't hurt to have a few people who are close to you review your application as well! Here at Penn, when reading applications (and yes, we read all of them), the admissions team is looking for all of the different thoughts, perspectives, interests, and experiences that our incoming students will bring to Penn. So let the real you shine through in your application, and if you do decide to apply, we can't wait to get to know you!                    

Learn About Penn's Comprehensive Review Process > <https://admissions.upenn.edu/how-to-apply/preparing-your-application?utm_campaign=ps-cy26&utm_content=uniquely-you-seniors&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>


                      Update your profile so we can send you the most accurate information and personalized invitations from Penn.                    


                          Follow @PreviewingPenn on social media for more admissions tips, campus life, and student takeovers!          


            University of Pennsylvania * Philadelphia, PA

emails.body:
Make your mark in Notre Dame, Indiana!

Kieran,
                                                                       

A Holy Cross education offers a small, personalized, and focused classroom environment, along with all the benefits of attending a larger university. Our close ties to the University of Notre Dame and Saint Mary's College triple the academic and social opportunities available to our students, including access to classes, student clubs and organizations, libraries, and athletic events ‚Äî all within walking distance from Holy Cross College.

                                    Some popular tri-campus opportunities that Holy Cross students take advantage of include:

	 Purchasing student tickets to Notre Dame home athletic games, including football games
	 Taking classes at both Notre Dame and Saint Mary's College without additional tuition charges
	 Accessing first-class research facilities such as Notre Dame's historic Hesburgh Library
	 Competing in club sports alongside other Notre Dame and Saint Mary's students

Want to join the tri-campus community? It all begins by applying today <https://www.hcc-nd.edu/applying-to-holy-cross/>!

                                    Ave Crux,

                                One of the best things about the Schmidthorst College of Business <https://www.bgsu.edu/business.html> at Bowling Green <http://bgsu.edu>, Kieran, is that you can make it exactly what you want it to be.                              

                                Our 12 specializations and 11 minors <https://www.bgsu.edu/business.html#majpro> mean that you can sharpen your focus while growing and finding your passion at the same time. There are 19 student organizations <https://www.bgsu.edu/business/students/student-organizations.html> in the Schmidthorst College of Business <https://www.bgsu.edu/business.html> in which you can meet like-minded students, improve your specific knowledge and skill sets and and get real-world experience that sets you apart. And, with many opportunities to study abroad <https://www.bgsu.edu/business/students/education-abroad.html>, you can broaden your knowledge even further.                              

                                We even have a 4+1 MBA program <https://www.bgsu.edu/academics/graduate/business-administration-full-time-program-masters.html> that allows you to use your college classes to get ahead and fast-track your way toward that specific role in a career you've been dreaming about. It's all here -- only at Bowling Green <http://bgsu.edu>.                                

Falcon Application <https://www.bgsu.edu/admissions/apply-now.html>                               

Apply to Bowling Green via the Falcon Application. You won't need a letter of recommendation, essay or even test scores ‚Äî it's super easy and super quick! If you'd rather, you can apply with the Common Application; be sure to only apply via one method, not both, though. 

                                After you apply, visit campus, so we can talk about our 200+ other majors <http://www.bgsu.edu/academics.html>, loads of support <http://www.bgsu.edu/life-design.html> and top career preparation <http://www.bgsu.edu/careerready.html>. emails.subject: December Updates From Cornerstone
emails.body:
decEMBER UPDATES
Happy December from Cornerstone University! As we enter the Christmas season, I look forward to sharing with you the latest of what's happening on Cornerstone's campus. Explore if Cornerstone could be your best-fit university!




DECEMBER VISITS & EVENTS
Campus visits are available from Dec. 1-11, 2025, after which visits are closed and reopen on Jan. 20, 2026. We would love to host you on campus before the end of the year!                            	 Dec. 1-11 | Campus visits <https://www.cornerstone.edu/admissions/visit-cornerstone/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect> available                              
	 Dec. 5 | Final fall Golden Eagle Visit Day <https://www.cornerstone.edu/admissions/visit-cornerstone/golden-eagle-days/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>, plus Symphonic Winds Christmas Concert <https://www.cornerstone.edu/events/symphonic-winds-christmas-concert/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>
	 Dec. 7 | Choral Christmas Concert <https://www.cornerstone.edu/events/choral-christmas-concert/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>






ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS
Applications are still open for incoming Fall 2026 students! I encourage you to apply before Christmas break so that you have time to also apply for any Cornerstone scholarships you might qualify for. You can begin your university application here.
Apply to Cornerstone <https://connect.cornerstone.edu/register/goldeneagles?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>





SCHOLARSHIP DEADLINES
We understand that affordability matters in your college decision. That's why we offer a variety of scholarship opportunities <https://www.cornerstone.edu/tuition-financial-aid/apply-for-aid/scholarships-grants/undergraduate-scholarships/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>! Check out the deadlines below:                            	                                 Jan. 10 | President's Fellows Program <https://www.cornerstone.edu/tuition-financial-aid/presidents-fellows-program/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>
	                                 Jan. 10 | Leadership Scholarship <https://www.cornerstone.edu/tuition-financial-aid/undergraduate-leadership-scholarships/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>
	                                 Jan. 10 | Missionary Family Scholarship <https://www.cornerstone.edu/tuition-financial-aid/undergraduate-leadership-scholarships/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>






FAFSA & FINANCIAL AID PACKAGES
Filing the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) <https://studentaid.gov/h/apply-for-aid/fafsa?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect> could qualify you for free money (grants) as well college loans. Be sure to add Cornerstone's school code (002266) so that we can receive your financial aid details and put together a package for you. Financial aid packages will be sent in January.

                            Plus, admitted students who submit the FAFSA with our school code by December 15 will be entered into drawings for one-time scholarships valued up to $1,000. Apply to Cornerstone <https://connect.cornerstone.edu/register/goldeneagles?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect> and submit the FAFSA <https://studentaid.gov/h/apply-for-aid/fafsa?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect> for the chance to qualify! If selected, students must enroll at Cornerstone beginning Fall 2026 to receive their scholarship.




ZEEMEE LIVE CHAT | DEC. 15
Tune in on the ZeeMee student app for our "Hot Cocoa & Chill" college live chat. Meet new faces, hear from Cornerstone students, and be entered into a giveaway for some CU swag! Download ZeeMee and then join us in the CU Live chat channel.

Date & Time: Monday, Dec 15, at 7:30 p.m. (ET)
Download ZeeMee <https://zeemee.app.link/cornerstone?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>





EVENT: CREATED TO DISCOVER
Interested in science, technology, engineering and mathematics? Join us on Cornerstone's campus in Grand Rapids, Michigan, for an evening that will take you hands-on into the world of STEM. Learn more and register for Created to Discover: Where Faith and Science Intersect.

Date & Time: Monday, Feb. 23 at 6:30 p.m. (ET)
Event Details <https://www.cornerstone.edu/news-events-blogs/events/stem-workshop/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>






CHRISTMAS BREAK
The Admissions Office will be closed for Christmas Break from Wednesday, Dec. 24 through Thursday, Jan. 1. If you would like to connect with your admissions counselor before the end of the year, be sure to do so soon!




If you have any questions, don't hesitate to call our office at 616.222.1426 or reply back to me.

                      Blessings,
Colleen Cox, B.S. '10, MBA '19
          Executive Director of Admissions




Contact Us <https://www.cornerstone.edu/about/contact/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>

Visit Campus <https://www.cornerstone.edu/admissions/visit-cornerstone/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>

Apply Now <https://www.cornerstone.edu/admissions/apply/?utm_campaign=prosp_decnews_fa26_fe&utm_content=email_1&utm_medium=email&utm_source=connect>




                              Copyright ¬© 2025, Cornerstone University
                              1001 E Beltline Ave NE, Grand Rapids, MI 49525

]

Dear Kieran,

I would really like to consider you for admission to the University of
Denver. I urge you to apply to DU [
https://my.denveradmission.du.edu/f/r/5534da6061e4566bab19cf43f?%3D%3D&
] by our January 15 Regular Decision
and Early Decision II (binding) deadline.

Click here to go to your application. [
https://my.denveradmission.du.edu/f/r/5534da6061e4566bab19cf43f?%3D%3D&
]

I‚Äôm waiving your application fee because I really want to see you
apply and I don‚Äôt want the fee to get in the way. Simply enter the
code DU26 when prompted.

Know that DU is a test-optional university and does not require test
scores. However, if you've already taken the SAT or ACT and feel that
your scores are an accurate representation of your academic abilities
and potential, feel free to submit your test scores for consideration.

Education is an adventure, and at DU, the world is your classroom. If
you want to conduct research, develop global perspectives while
studying abroad, help launch new businesses or do all this and more,
you'll find the resources for success at DU. Choose the Denver
Difference and explore all that you can do at DU.

I look forward to reviewing your application [
https://my.denveradmission.du.edu/f/r/5534da6061e4566bab19cf43f?%3D%3D&
]!

Sincerely,

Todd Rinehart
Vice Chancellor for Enrollment
University of Denver
2197 S. University Blvd.
Denver, CO 80208-9401

¬†

P.S. While our invitation to apply is intended for any application
cycle, you may want to consider applying Early Decision II. Students
admitted during our binding Early Decision rounds receive an
additional $5,000 merit aid award, and top academic performers will
have their full demonstrated financial need met. Additionally, Early
Decision applicants enjoy stronger consideration for admission and
benefit from earlier admission and financial aid notifications.

We received your information from
your Appily college research.

Browse to https://my.denveradmission.du.edu/email/unsubscribe/6930738ee63a0606976892/pulp-flint-maybe@duck.com/b4822ee8b2bfedecad98cbb87b5ed0b5ed69b22ca3aa92863ab0660c790ce99f to no longer receive emails from this company.

emails.subject: Arete = Excellence | Earn College Credit This Summer at the University of Dallas
emails.body:
·ºÄœÅŒµœÑŒÆ, aret·∏ó = Excellence

Experience college life with the classics this summer! 



                                Dear Kieran,

Are you looking for an educational and socially enriching experience this summer? Look no further than the University of Dallas' summer program Arete: An Introduction to the Classics <https://udallas.edu/arete?utm_campaign=hs-arete&utm_content=arete&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>. Join us to be inspired by great ideas, and experience the camaraderie that develops around them. 

                                At Arete: An Introduction to the Classics <https://udallas.edu/arete?utm_campaign=hs-arete&utm_content=arete&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>, you'll spend two weeks exploring excellence and the noble life. You will focus on the ancient Greek philosophical and literary tradition (Plato, Aristotle and Sophocles), the medieval and Renaissance tradition (Sir Gawain and the Green Knight, Shakespeare) and modern poetry and stories (Keats, Hopkins, Wilbur and Flannery O'Connor). With a broad perspective on the Western tradition, you will discover how ancient ideas continue to shape and inform contemporary thought and discourse.

You'll also earn three hours of college credit from the University of Dallas, the preeminent Catholic liberal arts university in the nation. You will attend lectures by University of Dallas faculty members and seminars led by UDallas PhD students, as well as view films, write essays, give an oral presentation, visit celebrated art museums, and attend a production at Shakespeare in the Park. The two-week program, including room and board on campus in a dorm residence hall, on-campus meals and activities, is $945.

                                Space is limited. Get more information and apply at udallas.edu/arete by March 1.

Here's what previous attendees have to say about Arete:
 
"I have been introduced to lifelong friends that I would never have met if it had not been for the Arete program. Being able to bond with others through the love of the classics is something I could not have found anywhere else."

ALEXANDRA MASSICCI-FUENTES, 2024 PARTICIPANT

"Arete opened up the entire Western Tradition before my eyes and heart. I now see just how amazing the philosophical life is, and that it is worth living."

GRAHAM MULLER, 2023 PARTICIPANT


     REGISTER TODAY <https://udallas.edu/arete?utm_campaign=hs-arete&utm_content=arete&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>    



                                                             



View email in browser. <https://ugadmis.udallas.edu/go?cmd=message&id=30596d67-8501-4a38-adb9-14514748a253&utm_campaign=hs-arete&utm_content=arete&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate>

emails.subject: üìù Spring 2026 On-Campus | How To Register and Important Links
emails.body:
Kieran,

                  Registering for spring on-campus classes is as easy as 1-2-3!

                  Use your Cedarville username and password to complete the links in the steps below to request your spring 2026 on-campus courses. You can reset your password here <https://cedarville.teamdynamix.com/TDClient/2045/Portal/KB/ArticleDet?ID=46509> if needed. If you have any difficulty, please contact IT during business hours at 937-766-7905. Be sure to tell them you are a Dual Enrollment (DE) student and do not use Self-Service to register for courses.
                                   

1. Sign Your Financial Terms and Conditions <https://selfservice.cedarville.edu/CedarInfo/FinancialResponsibility> 

	 Choose spring semester 2026.


                  2. Complete the Spring 2026 On-Campus Course Request Form <https://connect.cedarville.edu/register/?id=f8c7bf8c-c409-4eb3-9e22-1e0bc526ed62> 

	 Due to high demand for on-campus courses, please make sure to check the course schedule for availability.
	 Once you fully submit the form, your on-campus course request is final. View registration deadlines here <https://www.cedarville.edu/admissions/dual-enrollment/deadlines>.


                  3. Wait for Your Registration Confirmation Email

	 Please allow 5--10 business days for processing.
	 You may check your registration status in MyCU to view your class schedule <https://mycu.cedarville.edu/collection/all/dual-enrollment> for the spring 2026 semester.


                  Questions? Click here <https://www.cedarville.edu/admissions/dual-enrollment/general-faq#header-courseandregistrationquestions> for additional information or reply to this email if you need assistance.

                  Thank you,
                  Kristen Kenniv 

Cedarville University | 251 N Main St | Cedarville, OH 45314 | 1-800-CEDARVILLE | www.cedarville.edu

emails.subject: Kieran, Your Personalized Accepted Portal Is Ready!
emails.body:
Kieran,                              



                                As a reminder, now that you have been admitted to Cedarville University, we have created a personalized, interactive web portal just for you. Log in <https://www.cedarville.edu/checkstatus> today! This online resource site will alert you to required forms and approaching deadlines ‚Äî everything you need to know and do as you prepare for your enrollment at Cedarville!                              



Log in to your portal today! <https://www.cedarville.edu/checkstatus>

                                You'll find a few next steps already posted. Here are two highlights:                              



	1. Submit Your Enrollment Deposit                                      Submit the $250 enrollment deposit once your decision is finalized. Enrollment deposits are fully refundable prior to May 1, 2026 (for the fall 2026 term). You will be registered for classes and assigned campus housing in deposit-date order, so we encourage you to submit your deposit <https://cedarville.edu/deposit> as soon as possible.                                    


	2. Complete the FAFSA (if you have not done so already)                                      The Free Application for Federal Student Aid <https://fafsa.gov/> (FAFSA) is used to determine eligibility for all forms of need-based aid. Even if you do not anticipate qualifying for federal aid (like the Pell Grant), filling out the FAFSA will make you eligible to receive need-based scholarships from Cedarville and access subsidized student loans. The FAFSA is only for United States citizens and permanent United States residents. The FAFSA is open now, so fill yours out today!                                     





                                Congratulations again on your acceptance to Cedarville University! We are excited to have you take the next steps to join us on campus!                              





                        ‚Ää                      

                        ‚Ää                      
Follow Us on Social


                        ‚Ää

emails.subject: Your application advantages have been extended
Register | Dual Degree Program Info Sessions
emails.from: Columbia University School of General Studies <gs-admit_at_columbia.edu_jkgwnjk4@duck.com>
emails.body:
Join us online to learn about the Dual Degree Programs

              The International Dual Degree Programs <https://gs.columbia.edu/content/international-dual-degree-programs?utm_campaign=ug_admissions_events_f25&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate> at the Columbia University School of General Studies (GS) offer students a unique global undergraduate experience with the opportunity to immerse themselves in distinct academic, social, and cultural environments at world-renowned universities.            

              Dual Degree students spend years one and two at either Sciences Po, France's leading university for the social sciences, Trinity College Dublin, Ireland's premier university, Tel Aviv University, Israel's leading liberal arts institution, or City University of Hong Kong, China's hub for innovative research, before continuing their studies at Columbia University in years three and four. Upon completion of the Programs, students earn two bachelor's degrees‚Äîone from Columbia, and one from our partner university.            


              Virtual Information Sessions            

              Join an admissions officer and current students of the International Dual Degree Programs to learn about academics, financial aid, admissions, and more. Registration is required.

Tuesday, December 2
                      Sciences Po Dual Degree Program Q&A with Current Students                    

                      5 - 6 p.m.                    


Wednesday, December 3
                      Tel Aviv University Dual Degree Program Q&A with Current Students                    

                      5 - 6 p.m.                    


Thursday, December 4
                      Trinity College Dublin Dual Degree Program Q&A with Current Students                    

                      5 - 6 p.m.                    


Sunday, December 7
                      City University of Hong Kong Joint Bachelor's Degree Program Online Information Session                    

                      10 - 11:30 a.m.                    




              ADVISING APPOINTMENTS            

              Schedule a phone or in-person appointment to speak individually with an admissions representative. For general program information and the application process, please meet with a Columbia GS Admissions Officer. For questions about the International Dual Degree programs including student life, academics and their experience in our programs, please meet with a current student.

              Appointments are typically 20-30 minutes long. There are a limited amount of spaces available, so please register right away. Please note all times are in the Eastern time zone. Note that current students are enrolled in one of Columbia's International Dual Degree Programs with Sciences Po, Trinity College Dublin, or Tel Aviv University and are not able to answer specific questions about the admissions process.             

                      Meet with an Admissions Officer                    


                      Meet with a Current Student                    







This email was sent to jkgwnjk4@duck.com by Columbia University School of General Studies.

emails.subject: Kieran, Deposit Today To Reserve Your Place at Cedarville
emails.body:
Submit your deposit to secure your spot in the incoming class!

      Submit your deposit to secure your spot in the incoming class!    
                                Dear Kieran,                               

                                Congratulations again on your admission to Cedarville University! We're excited about the possibility of welcoming you to a campus that's growing and thriving ‚Äî last year alone, we enrolled more than 1,300 new students and received record applications.                              

                                To make sure you don't miss out on the best options, please submit your $250 enrollment deposit soon. Here's why acting now matters:                              



	 Early housing selection: Students who deposit first get first access to housing selection, which means more choices for residence halls and roommates. 
	 Avoid the waitlist: With record interest, some programs and housing options may fill quickly. Submitting your deposit secures your place in the incoming class and keeps you from being waitlisted.                                 



Ready to claim your spot?
                                Submit your deposit here: cedarville.edu/deposit
                                Amount: $250
Student ID: 2742467

                                If you have any questions about housing, financial aid, or the deposit process, we're here to help at admissions@cedarville.edu or 1-800-CEDARVILLE.  Also, your deposit is fully refundable prior to May 1, 2026!                              

                                We can't wait to see how you'll grow and contribute at Cedarville. Let's make it official!                              

                                Sincerely,                               





Kora Arminio 
                                Director of Undergraduate Admissions 
                                Cedarville University                               





‚Ää


                                Cedarville University | 251 N Main St. | Cedarville, OH 45314 | 1-800-CEDARVILLE | cedarville.edu

emails.subject: You‚Äôre invited to apply, Kieran.
emails.body:
Hi Kieran,

      I hope you've enjoyed learning more about DBU. We're a community grounded in truth because of our unshakable foundation in faith. I think you would fit in perfectly.

      So, I'm thrilled to invite you to apply to DBU <https://apply.dbu.edu/apply/?sr=2d9b9a5f-2e20-4e41-8d82-3414f2648d32&utm_campaign=senior-search&utm_content=senior-search-10&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=apply> as soon as possible!

      Here's what to do next:    

	         Complete the online DBU application <https://apply.dbu.edu/apply/?sr=2d9b9a5f-2e20-4e41-8d82-3414f2648d32&utm_campaign=senior-search&utm_content=senior-search-10&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=apply>.      
	 Visit our campus <https://www.dbu.edu/visit/?utm_campaign=senior-search&utm_content=senior-search-10&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=apply> if you haven't already.      
	         Watch your email for your acceptance letter.      

      If you have any questions about taking these next steps, feel free to contact me. I'm eager to help and look forward to receiving your application <https://apply.dbu.edu/apply/?sr=2d9b9a5f-2e20-4e41-8d82-3414f2648d32&utm_campaign=senior-search&utm_content=senior-search-10&utm_medium=email&utm_source=carnegie-slate&utm_term=apply>!

      Go Patriots!

      Grant Pierce
      Senior Admissions Counselor

emails.subject: Connect 1:1 with an Admissions Representative
emails.from: Columbia University International Dual Degree Programs <gs-admit_at_columbia.edu_jkgwnjk4@duck.com>
emails.body:
Schedule an advising appointment to learn more

              Connect with Admissions            


              Dear Kieran,

              You're invited to register for an advising appointment with an admissions officer or current International Dual Degree Program student to learn more about the International Dual Degree Programs <https://www.gs.columbia.edu/content/international-dual-degree-programs?utm_campaign=ug_admissions_events_f23&utm_medium=email&utm_source=slate> at Columbia University School of General Studies (GS).  

              The International Dual Degree Programs offer students unique global undergraduate experiences with the opportunity to immerse themselves in distinct academic, social, and cultural environments at world-renowned universities.

              Dual Degree students spend years one and two at either Sciences Po, France's leading university for the social sciences, Trinity College Dublin, Ireland's premier university, Tel Aviv University, Israel's leading liberal arts institution, or City University of Hong Kong, China's innovative research university addressing global issues, before continuing their studies at Columbia University in years three and four. Upon completion of the Programs, students earn two bachelor's degrees‚Äîone from Columbia, and one from our partner university.            


              Meet with an admissions officer            

              Schedule a phone or in-person appointment to speak individually with an admissions representative. For general program information and the application process, please meet with a Columbia GS Admissions Officer. Appointments are typically 20-30 minutes long. There are a limited amount of spaces available, so please register right away. Please note all times are in the Eastern time zone. 


              meet with a current student            

              Schedule a phone or in-person appointment to speak individually with an admissions representative. For questions about the International Dual Degree programs including student life, academics and their experience in our programs, please meet with a current student. Please be advised that current students are enrolled in one of Columbia's International Dual Degree Programs with Sciences Po, Trinity College Dublin, or Tel Aviv University and are not able to answer specific questions about the admissions process. Appointments are typically 20-30 minutes long. There are a limited amount of spaces available, so please register right away. Please note all times are in the Eastern time zone. 





This email was sent to jkgwnjk4@duck.com by Columbia University International Dual Degree Programs.

emails.subject: Your Purdue degree minus the financial baggage
emails.body:
Hi Kieran,


                                  You're probably starting to consider the cost of a quality college degree.

emails.subject: ‚òÉÔ∏è It's December! Have You Applied to Denison?
emails.body:
With a little over a month before our final application deadline, now is the time to get everything in order!

            How is it already December?

          Hello Kieran,        

          December marks the start of beautiful snow falls, peppermint treats, and cozy afternoons watching football ‚Äî or binging The Office for the hundredth time. For the Denison Office of Admission, December means reading applications. December also marks our deadline to apply for the $25,000 per year Ohio Scholarship <https://denison.edu/campus/admission/ohio-initiative>. We know you'll think Denison is an amazing institution, and we just don't want you to miss your chance to get that application in front of us.        

Start my Application! <https://apply.commonapp.org/login?ma=77&tref=N1013>
          Denison offers students small class sizes, great relationships, and an incredible amount of opportunities ‚Äî academic or just for fun ‚Äî all to prepare you for a successful life beyond college. And though we're sure you've heard that line from several other colleges, how many other schools are putting you in the driver seat for your education? We don't require an application fee or supplemental essay, nor do we require standardized testing, so why wouldn't you apply? Just remember, the final deadline to apply is January 15. To qualify for the guaranteed Ohio Scholarship <https://denison.edu/campus/admission/ohio-initiative> you'll need to submit your application today ‚Äî additional materials such as your transcript or recommendation letters can arrive at a later date.

          We look forward to seeing an application from you soon! Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have questions <mailto:admission@denison.edu> or need additional information.        

          Best wishes,        

          Denison University Office of Admission

        


      Denison University Office of Admission
100 West College Street, Granville, Ohio, 43023 <https://www.google.com/maps/place/100+W+College+St,+Granville,+OH+43023/>

emails.subject: Apply for the President's Ministry Impact Scholarship
emails.body:
Kieran,



                                If you have a parent who is in full-time ministry at a church, Christian school, camp, or other parachurch organization, you qualify to apply for the President's Ministry Impact Scholarship <https://www.cedarville.edu/financialaid/President-s-Ministry-Impact-Scholarship> at Cedarville University. This scholarship celebrates Cedarville's strong support of the local church and those who invest their lives in full-time vocational ministry.                              

                                Students who are selected for the scholarship may be awarded up to $7,000, which is renewable for all four years if you meet academic requirements.                               

                                If you fit the criteria for this scholarship, go online <https://www.cedarville.edu/financialaid/President-s-Ministry-Impact-Scholarship> to learn more about this scholarship and apply. The application deadline is February 15, 2026.                              





                        ‚Ää                      

                        ‚Ää                      
Follow Us on Social


                        ‚Ää

¬†

want to remind you that the
December 1 application deadline is
quickly approaching!¬†

].

¬†

The best part? There's no application fee or required test-score
submission!

¬†

All full-time, incoming undergraduate students receive the Main Street
Scholarship, an award starting at $80,000, applied over four years.
But the Main Street Scholarship is just the beginning! This
scholarship is "stackable," meaning that it can be combined with other
awards and aid, including:

* The Capital Merit Scholarship: Given for academic accomplishments
and based on GPA.

* The Comet Community Award: A $5,000 award for residential students
that is applied to housing.

* The Capital Gateway Scholarship: Full tuition and fees are awarded
to students who meet additional GPA, residency, and incoming
requirements.

emails.subject: Take the world by STORM
emails.body:
Dear Kieran,

 

I want to make sure you know you are on Lake Erie College's radar!
You're invited to submit your STORM Application [
https://my.lec-info.org/f/r/b6eb082ea781c763d6a1486cc?&
] as soon as possible.

 

To make applying easier, we ask for no application fee and test scores
are optional. Plus, we won't keep you waiting ‚Äì you'll receive an
admission decision within two weeks of submitting your application
materials. You'll also be considered for scholarships automatically.

 

You may even apply to LEC with the Common App [
https://my.lec-info.org/f/r/920c18dda092b99178974d904?%3D%3D&
] if you prefer. You'll enjoy all the advantages mentioned above.

 

I chose you to apply because you seem like someone who wants to see
the world become a better place, and LEC won't ask you to abandon that
vision. We base our curriculum around the idea that you _can_ effect
change, and we'll help you develop the skills that make action happen.

 

That's a long way of saying: _You'll take the world by storm,
Kieran._

 

I can't wait to learn more about you when I receive your STORM
Application [
https://my.lec-info.org/f/r/b6eb082ea781c763d6a1486cc?&
] or the Common App [
https://my.lec-info.org/f/r/920c18dda092b99178974d904?%3D%3D&
]. 

 

Sincerely,

Ashley Mayse, MBA
Vice President for Enrollment
Lake Erie College
391 W Washington St
Painesville, Ohio 44077

[
https://my.lec-info.org/f/r/f616f8bda0b4f167497b5a61b?%2FdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPWNyb3NzJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9ZW5yb2xsMzYwJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9bGVhcm4mdXRtX3Rlcm09c2lnbmVyJnRubnQ9M2YyMGMzYjYtOTM5Yi00NjlmLThmNDQtZDZmOTJmNWViMjUxJlVUTV9yY3JkPWFhYjUxZjdkLWQwNmYtNDNjNy04YjAwLTQ4YzA5ZDQ5ZjZjZCI7fQ%3D%3D&

emails.subject: Am I reaching Kieran?
Re: Your admission decision at Saint Xavier University
emails.body:
Your status is proof that you've impressed our admission team ...

Dear Kieran,

Your Priority Student status is proof that you've impressed our admission team at Saint Xavier University, and the advantages that come with that status demonstrate that we're interested in your candidacy.

If you haven't yet done so, submit the Priority Student Application we've created for you here or add SXU to the Common App. The deadline to apply is December 15, but that should be no problem. Your advantages are seriously time-saving. You'll:

  • Receive an annual scholarship worth up to $24,000 upon admission.
  • Pay no application fee.
  • Write no essay (unless you are a nursing applicant).
  • Submit no test scores unless you want to.

We want it to be simple to complete our application, Kieran, and we want our top-tier education to be within your reach. That's why we offer a wide range of scholarships and awards to qualified students‚Äîand why we're happy to consider you for those awards automatically when you apply.

Submit the Priority Student Application here.

Or add SXU to the Common App here.

I hope you'll take a few moments to submit your application right now, Kieran! I look forward to learning even more about you.

Sincerely,

Brian D. Hotzfield
Vice President - Enrollment
Saint Xavier University
3700 West 103rd Street
Chicago, IL 60655

                                      Hello Kieran,
